          stepNumber: 1,
          instruction: "FOR THE BEANS: Place beans, ham, bay leaves, water, and baking soda in large saucepan with tight-fitting lid. Bring to boil over medium-high heat; using large spoon, skim foam as it rises to surface. Stir in salt, reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer briskly until beans are tender, 11/4 to 11/2 hours (if necessary, add 1 cup more water and continue to simmer until beans are tender); do not drain beans. Discard bay leaves. Remove ham steak (ham steak darkens to color of beans), cut it into 1/4-inch cubes, and set aside."
